title: Jeevan Mrityu
subTitle: Upon his release from exile, Ashok's life turns upside down when he learns about his mother's death and the truth behind his false accusation.

title: Ardh Satya
subTitle: Anant, a righteous police officer, is torn between his ethics and dishonest practices in the police department. Soon, he discovers the strong connection between corruption and politics.

title: Painter Babu
subTitle: After an unexpected blow to his father's business, Shyam, who loves Renu, is forced to marry Menaka. Unhappy with the decision, he becomes a rebel and invites more troubles in his life.

title: Chitchor
subTitle: When Geeta's sister arranges her wedding with a young engineer, their father mistakenly brings the wrong man home. However, as love blossoms between the two, the arrival of a letter startles everyone.

title: Dada
subTitle: Jeetu works as a mechanic, lives in a slum area and is all set to marry Kamini, the girl he loves. But his life is destroyed when he is arrested and convicted for killing Kamini's brother.

title: Qayamat
subTitle: Two close friends turn enemies when one becomes a criminal and the other, an IPS officer. Wronged by his friend, the criminal swears to take revenge once he returns from prison.

title: Teesri Aankh
subTitle: Mali brings up an orphan baby boy as her own. Later, when her husband reveals the real identity of the child, she strives to cope with the truth.

title: Kalicharan
subTitle: When Prabhakar, an honest cop, is murdered by Din Dayal, a powerful crime lord, Khanna recruits his doppelganger Kalicharan to defeat Din Dayal.

title: Kranti
subTitle: Sanga, a devout employee of Raja Laxman Singh, is falsely accused of killing him. He escapes prison and forms a group of revolutionaries with the sole aim of driving the British out of India.

title: Khilona Bana Khalnayak
subTitle: Tatya Vinchu, a dying gangster, transfer his soul into a doll. The ventriloquist Lakshya unknowingly brings the sinister doll into his life, leading to chaos.

title: Khilona Bana Khalnayak
subTitle: Tatya Vinchu, a dying gangster, transfer his soul into a doll. The ventriloquist Lakshya unknowingly brings the sinister doll into his life, leading to chaos.

title: Zehreela Insaan
subTitle: Arjun, a short-tempered person, falls in love with Margaret, but her family is against their relationship. The couple elopes, but destiny forces the duo to commit suicide.

title: Priyatama
subTitle: Despite having made the difficult decision to separate, Dolly pretends to love her husband when her father comes to visit.

title: Mome Ki Gudiya
subTitle: Ravi falls in love with Sheel but is shocked to learn that her marriage is fixed with his father. Even after his father steps back and Ravi gets married to Sheel, dark secrets loom over the newlyweds.

title: Aap Ke Deewane
subTitle: Forced to become college dropouts, childhood friends Ram and Rahim put on quirky disguises to get hired as home tutors for a wealthy and sheltered woman. As they spend time with her, a love triangle starts taking shape.

title: Gopal Krishna
subTitle: King Kansa claims the throne of Mathura and kills off his nephews to prevent his death at one of their hands. However, the eighth child is whisked off to safety and grows up as Krishna.

title: Amrit
subTitle: A widowed man and woman face abuse from their respective children and seek comfort from each other instead.

title: Desh Premee
subTitle: Master Dinanath's life crumbles after he helps arrest Thakur Pratab Singh. Estranged from his wife and daughter, he relocates to a slum with his son Raju, who tragically falls into a life of crime.

title: Toofan
subTitle: Separated at birth, the paths of Shyam, a lousy magician unwittingly roped into a crime, and Toofan, a defender of the people, cross again years later as they reunite to avenge their father.

title: Balidaan
subTitle: Police Inspector Vijay makes an enemy of bandit Ranga after he kills one of his men. After the vengeful Ranga wilfully abducts Vijay's wife and daughter, he must race against time to save his family.

title: Balidaan
subTitle: Police Inspector Vijay makes an enemy of bandit Ranga after he kills one of his men. After the vengeful Ranga wilfully abducts Vijay's wife and daughter, he must race against time to save his family.

title: Hum Hindustani
subTitle: The Nath family faces hard times because of a property dispute. Things come to a head when one of the sons in the family is accused of theft.

title: Ponga Pandit
subTitle: Two fathers make arrangements and marry their young children. However, years later when the nuptials are almost finalised, the girl rejects the boy.

title: Madhumati
subTitle: Deven takes shelter in a mansion when a landslide blocks his route to the railway station. He finds the mansion eerily familiar and soon learns about the story of his previous birth.

title: Leader
subTitle: Vijay is a rebellious law student who boldly criticises the government, flirts with a beautiful woman and invites trouble. But his life changes when he is accused of assassinating a politician.

title: Naya Daur
subTitle: A man introduces a bus service in an attempt to make quick profits and endangers the peace and livelihood of local farmers and workers.

title: The Emperor of the Mughals
subTitle: A storm brews inside the royal palace and threatens to swallow up the entire kingdom, as a Mughal emperor's pride clashes with the blossoming love between his son and a court dancer.

title: Ganga Jamuna
subTitle: Ganga and Jumna, two orphaned brothers, grow up to find themselves on opposite sides of the law when one becomes a police officer and the other turns into a dreaded gangster.

title: Saudagar
subTitle: Moti betrays his loyal wife and business partner, Majubee, to marry his true love, Phoolbanu. However, his selfish act unleashes unforeseen consequences that upend his life.
